==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Anthelmintic
<hw>An`thel*min"tic</hw></mhw>
<pr>(⟦acr⟧n`th⟦ecr⟧l*m⟦icr⟧n"t⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>anti-</ets> + Gr. <grk>"e`lmins</grk>, <grk>-inqos</grk>, worm,
esp. a tapeworm, or mawworm. See also <er>helminth</er>]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>capable of expelling or destroying parasitic
worms.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>An anthelmintic
remedy.</def></def2> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>anthelminthic</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> helminthic, parasiticidal</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

